text: Krivle-Ilyushkino () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Krivle-Ilyushkinsky Selsoviet, Kuyurgazinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 678 as of 2010. There are 4 streets. == Geography == It is located 23 km from Yermolayevo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Kuyurgazinsky District
title: Krivle-Ilyushkino
